parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or fails to shift into gear
the transmission slips or jerks
the vehicle loses power or acceleration
the engine RPMs fluctuate
and the vehicle may roll or move unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shifter failure can cause the vehicle to roll or move unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shifter fails to engage or disengage
the vehicle rolls or moves unexpectedly
the vehicle fails to shift into gear
and the gear shifter feels loose or stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: ESC failure can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The ESC warning light illuminates
the vehicle loses traction or stability
the vehicle skids or slides
and the vehicle's brakes or engine power are reduced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine misfires
the engine RPMs fluctuate
the engine stalls or dies
and the vehicle loses power or acceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various safety issues, including the malfunction of airbags, brake lights, and traction control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains illuminated
the brake lights fail to illuminate or illuminate unnecessarily
the traction control warning light illuminates
and the vehicle experiences reduced engine power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of braking ability.
symptoms: The brake lights fail to illuminate or illuminate unnecessarily
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the vehicle experiences reduced braking power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause injuries or fatalities in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The airbag warning light remains illuminated
and the airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The reduction of engine power can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences reduced engine power
and the "reduced engine power" warning light illuminates.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the traction control system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: The traction control warning light illuminates
and the vehicle experiences reduced traction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger airbag sensor can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The passenger airbag light alternates between on and off
the service airbag light comes on
the passenger airbag sensor fails to detect an adult passenger
the airbag warning light flashes or remains on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag module can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The service airbag light comes on
the airbag warning light flashes or remains on
the airbag module needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical issues with the airbag system can cause the airbag to not deploy in the event of a crash, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The service airbag light comes on
the airbag warning light flashes or remains on
the airbag system is not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in a crash
the airbag warning light was on prior to the crash.
